n Rmd file (left in image) that show up as shown below (right in image). Emphasizing Words To italisize a word use the asterisk (Shift 8) *italisize*. To bold a word use the double asterisk **bold**. The back tic can be used tohighlightwords by placing back tics on each side of a word: highlight `. Bullet Points Simple Lists To achieve the result: This is the first item. This is the second. This is the third. Use the code: To achieve the result: * This is the first item. * This is the second. * This is the third. Numbered Lists To achieve the result: This is the first item. This is the second. This is the third. Use the code: To achieve the result: 1. This is the first item. 2. This is the second. 3. This is the third. Lettered Lists To achieve the result: This is the first item. This is the second. This is the third. Use the code: To achieve the result: A) This is the first item. B) This is the second. C) This is the third. Nested Lists What is \(2+2\)? 4 8 What is \(3	imes5\)? 14 15 1. What is $2+2$? a. **4** b. 8 2. What is $3	imes5$? a. 14 b. **15** Math Equations Use the dollar signs $x=5$ to write \(x=5\) or $z= rac{x-\mu}{\sigma}$ to write \(z= rac{x-\mu}{\sigma}\). For a nicely centered equation use the double dollar signs $$ $$ on separate lines $$ z =  rac{ ar{x}-\mu}{ rac{\sigma}{\sqrt{n}}} $$ to get \[ z =  rac{ ar{x}-\mu}{ rac{\sigma}{\sqrt{n}}} \] Or $$ H_0: \mu_	ext{Group 1} = \mu_	ext{Group 2} $$ $$ H_a: \mu_	ext{Group 1} 
